# JobFinder — configuration for `docker compose up`.
#
#   cp .env.example .env    # then edit .env (it is gitignored; never commit keys)
#
# Placeholder values only in this file — real keys go in your local .env.

# REQUIRED — your Anthropic API key (https://console.anthropic.com/).
# Read server-side only. Powers the resume rewrite and change explanation
# (Claude Sonnet) and, only if you switch Settings to the Anthropic scoring
# backend, scoring (Claude Haiku). Scoring defaults to the free local
# Ollama sidecar, which needs no key.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-REPLACE_ME

# OPTIONAL — RapidAPI key for the Greenhouse aggregator source
# (fantastic.jobs "Active Jobs DB" on rapidapi.com). Leave blank to skip:
# the Greenhouse toggle in Settings only takes effect when a key is present.
RAPID_API_KEY=

# OPTIONAL — the local scoring model the Ollama sidecar pre-pulls on first
# start. Default (when unset): qwen3:4b-instruct-2507-q4_K_M — a ~2.5 GB
# download that runs on CPU in ~4-5 GB RAM.
#
# Higher-accuracy upgrade path (wants a ~16 GB GPU): uncomment the line
# below to pre-pull batiai/qwen3.6-27b:iq3 (~11 GB), then enter the same
# model name in Settings -> Ollama model so the app scores with it.
# Eval evidence for both choices: docs/scoring-model-eval.md.
#OLLAMA_MODEL=batiai/qwen3.6-27b:iq3
